feedback: A little disappointed to see the crabs were in plastic bags this week - I know its challenging to transport these via your current system to delivery/pick up, but live crabs, lobsters, etc shouldn't be stored in closed plastic bags unless they have lots of holes for them to breathe - and not sure they should be in a closed cooler for the same reason. Picked mine up on the earlier side of the pick up time frame and when we got them home, they were barely alive. Had to cook them right away to ensure they'd still be good. Don't know if theres a solution to this, but don't think I'll be ordering live shellfish unless this is resolved.

primary_motivations: Environmental sustainabilty, Connecting to community, Supporting the local economy
feedback: I think what you do and offer is amazing. I have customer service quibbles - not about the personalities people who answer the phones or emails, you're all lovely - but about the information you give. I'm a home cook who believes in supporting food companies across the country who are working on behalf of sustainable farming and fishing, heirloom grains and beans- I buy tahini from Soom Foods, subscribe to Givens' farms CSA boxes, ButcherBox, D'artagnan, Anson Mills, to name a few. Your quality is absolutely up there with these places, but your customer service is not. Giovanni's in Morro Bay gives very quick and informed advice about, for example, how to store oysters. I did not get good advice about storing oysters when I contacted you. When I used to pick up my share at Gladdens I found it very frustrating that you didn't have a more exact time. The first time I got a home delivery you called and said the driver “wanted to reach out to me” - words that donor inspire consumer confidence. I don't want the driver to reach out to me because his technology didn't get my address right and he's hoping to deliver my fish the next day. I want my fish delivered. This is why I thought two weeks ago of discontinuing my subscription to GetHooked. But I've decided, because of your superb product, and the fact your hearts are in the right place to give it time. ??
name: Polly Frost
